wiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PunctuatedForEmphasis" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PunctuatedForEmphasis">Punctuated! For! Emphasis!</a>: Kogorr does this when <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">he lures Heroman into a vulnerable position by using a false weakness as bait.</span><div class="indent"><strong>Kogorr:</strong> <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Sorry, but... my weak point... is... <strong>not... THERE!</strong></span></div></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PuppeteerParasite" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PuppeteerParasite">Puppeteer Parasite</a>: How the Skrugg are <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">controlling Will and Nick. It's <em>not</em> consensual, and Will has a breakdown when he hears Lina's voice.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RapidFireTyping" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RapidFireTyping">Rapid-Fire Typing</a>: Denton does this to stop the spheres.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ReasonableAuthorityFigure" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ReasonableAuthorityFigure">Reasonable Authority Figure</a>: Agent Hughes ultimately turns out to be this in episode 15. Shame he has <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MadScientist" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MadScientist">Dr. Minami</a> working alongside him.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RivalTurnedEvil" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RivalTurnedEvil">Rival Turned Evil</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">As it turns out, the two assassins in episode five are Will and Nick.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Robosexual" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Robosexual">Robosexual</a>: Following the events of Episode 16, <span class="spoiler" title